{
  "id": "019d286c-c8e3-7462-a4e5-9d86aeda1680",
  "content": "div class=\"slide\" style=\"background: linear-gradient(160deg, #0f172a 0%, #1a2332 50%, #0f172a 100%);\">\n  <div class=\"slide-label\">Key Takeaways</div>\n  <div class=\"slide-title\">\n    What I Learned<br>\n    <span class=\"highlight-green\">Today</span>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"takeaway-list\">\n    <div class=\"takeaway-item\">\n      <div class=\"takeaway-icon\">&#128161;</div>\n      <div class=\"takeaway-text\">\n        <strong>Question the OS, not just the hardware.</strong><br>\n        <span style=\"color: var(--text-secondary);\">Linux uses ~1 GB idle vs Windows' 5 GB+. That's 4 GB back for your containers.</span>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"takeaway-item\">\n      <div class=\"takeaway-icon\">&#127918;</div>\n      <div class=\"takeaway-text\">\n        <strong>Know where your GPU power goes.</strong><br>\n        <span style=\"color: var(--text-secondary);\">A text editor doesn't need an RTX 3060. Linux lets you choose per-app.</span>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"takeaway-item\">\n      <div class=\"takeaway-icon\">&#128268;</div>\n      <div class=\"takeaway-text\">\n        <strong>Check your cable wiring.</strong><br>\n        <span style=\"color: var(--text-secondary);\">HDMI vs USB-C can mean the difference between GPU always-on and GPU idle.</span>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"takeaway-item\">\n      <div class=\"takeaway-icon\">&#129300;</div>\n      <div class=\"takeaway-text\">\n        <strong>The best upgrade is understanding your system.</strong><br>\n        <span style=\"color: var(--text-secondary);\">Before buying more hardware, ask: is the software being efficient?</span>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"divider\" style=\"margin-top: 32px;\"></div>\n\n  <div style=\"text-align: center; margin-top: 24px;\">\n    <div style=\"font-size: 20px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-secondary); margin-bottom: 12px;\">\n      Have you tried dual-booting for development?\n    </div>\n    <div style=\"font-size: 18px; color: var(--text-muted);\">\n      Let me know your setup in the comments &#128071;\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"flex-grow\"></div>\n  <div class=\"author-tag\">Lim Chun Zhe</div>\n  <div class=\"slide-number\">08 / 08</div>\n</div>\n\n</body>\n</html>\n",
